name: ABC
description: Multi-talented and multi-membered Puck Collective returned to Pick Me Up with Puckleduster – their tattoo parlour. At Puckleduster you could sit in the tattoo chair and get a tattoo, exclusively designed by your favourtie Puck illustrator, using the classic ‘bubblegum pack’, water-based transfer technique. Along with the temporary tattoos, each Puck member produced a range of prints, tees, totes, zines and jewellery to sell at the event. This print by Alec-Doherty was produced as part of Puckleduster. It is a 2 colour Risograph print. Risograph 2013 Edition of 70 297 × 420mm

name: Cat Town
description: Welcome to the Town of Cats. Don't stay after dark lest their glowing eyes hold you in their gaze forever... This two colour screen print from Babycrow features a slightly metallic gun metal black that catches the light with a subtle sheen and phosphorescent pigment ink for the eyes which glows in the dark! Hand Pulled Screen Print Edition of 35 297 × 420mm

name: Witch Bones
description: These are the remains of Mary Bateman, aka “The Yorkshire Witch”. In the early 19th century, she was tried and executed for witchcraft and the murder of Rebecca Perigo. In a gruesome finale after her death, her body was put on public display where strips of skin were sold off as evil warding magic charms. What was left of her is now on display at Thackray Museum in Leeds… This screen print from Babycrow features a slightly metallic gun metal black that catches the light with a subtle sheen and is printed on 600gsm handmade cotton paper. Hand Pulled Screen Print Edition of 15 560 × 760mm
